'''哈爾曼迪爾·薩希卜'''（[[旁遮普語|旁遮普語]]: ਹਰਿਮੰਦਰ ਸਾਹਿਬ；{{lang-en|Harmandir Sahib}}），又名'''达尔巴尔·萨希卜'''（[[旁遮普語|旁遮普語]]: ਦਰਬਾਰ ਸਾਹਿਬ，读音[dəɾbɑɾ sɑhɪb]；{{lang-en|Darbar Sahib}}<ref>发音为Darbaar Saahib，见[http://www.gurbani.org/articles/webart160.htm HARMANDIR, gurbani, 2012-07-10] {{Wayback|url=http://www.gurbani.org/articles/webart160.htm |date=20150911232821 }}</ref>）<ref name=eos>{{cite web |url = http://www.learnpunjabi.org/eos/ |title = Harimandar |last1 = Kerr |first1 = Ian J. |website = Encyclopaedia of Sikhism |publisher = Punjabi University Patiala |access-date = 21 March 2015 |deadurl = yes |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140508213214/http://www.learnpunjabi.org/eos/ |archivedate = 2014年5月8日 }}</ref><ref>Golden Temple, Punjabi University, Parm Barkshish Singh, Devinder Kumar Verma, ''ISBN 978-81-7380-569-1''</ref><ref name=gao>高建章，锡克·辛格·阿卡利：锡克民族与锡克教，四川民族出版社，1994年，第67-71页</ref>，非正式俗称为'''金庙'''（{{lang-en|Golden Temple}}）<ref name=eos/>，位于[[印度|印度]][[旁遮普邦|旁遮普邦]][[阿姆利则|阿姆利则]]，是[[錫克教|錫克教]]最重要的{{Link-en|谒师所|gurdwara}}。

其所在都市[[阿姆利则|阿姆利则]]（直譯為''不老花蜜之池''）在公元1577年由[[錫克教|錫克教]]第四世{{Link-en|古鲁 (锡克教)|Sikh gurus|古鲁}}（[[上师|上师]]）{{Link-en|拉木達斯|Guru Ram Das}}開闢<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.amritsar.com/Golden%20Temple%20History.shtml |title=History, Harmandir Sahib, the Golden Temple, Amritsar |publisher=Amritsar Portal |accessdate=29 November 2014 |archive-date=2016-08-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160802020452/http://www.amritsar.com/Golden%20Temple%20History.shtml |dead-url=no }}</ref>，其後第五世古魯{{Link-en|阿爾瓊|Guru Arjun}}決定在此城中心設立谒师所哈爾曼迪爾·薩希卜，並在其中供奉錫克教經典[[古鲁·格兰特·萨希卜|古鲁·格兰特·萨希卜]]（或稱Adi Granth）<ref>薛克翘，中世纪锡克教文学概说，南亚研究2006年01期</ref><ref name=gao/><ref name="turkbook">İsmail Hâmi Danişmend, Osmanlı Devlet Erkânı, Türkiye Yayınevi, İstanbul, 1971 (Turkish)</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.omnilexica.com/?q=sahib |title=Sahib, omnilexica |accessdate=2015-04-19 |archive-date=2016-03-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304195412/http://www.omnilexica.com/?q=sahib |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=eos/>。第六世古魯{{Link-en|哈果濱|Guru Hargobind}}繼任後在此廟宇旁設立錫克教五大權位之席之一的[[永恒王座|永恒王座]]<ref name="Bhatti2013">{{cite book|author=S. S. Bhatti|title=Golden Temple: Marvel of Sikh Architecture|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=PJZWQQUyr1EC&pg=PA24|year=2013|publisher=Dorrance Publishing|isbn=978-1-4349-8964-2|pages=24–}}</ref>。

该庙的名字中，“哈尔曼迪尔”（旁遮普語：ਹਰਿਮੰਦਰ，{{lang-en|Harmandir}}）是由两个[[梵语|梵语]]词汇“Hari”和“Mandir”结合而来。“Hari”是无所不在的神的名字之一，字面意思是“除去所有灵性生活（Aatmic-Jeevan）之障碍者”。“Mandir”意思是“住宅，住处，居处，房子，宫殿，寺庙，住所”等等。所以“哈尔曼迪尔”的意思是“神之住所”或“神的庙”，通过这里可以体验到灵性的充分舒展<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.gurbani.org/articles/webart160.htm |title=HARMANDIR, gurbani, 2012-07-10 |accessdate=2015-04-19 |archive-date=2015-09-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150911232821/http://www.gurbani.org/articles/webart160.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref>。“萨希卜”（旁遮普語：ਸਾਹਿਬ，{{lang-en|Sahib}}）源于[[阿拉伯语|阿拉伯语]]（{{rtl-lang|ar|صاحب}}，{{lang-en|Sahib}}），意思是“持有者、拥有者、所有者”。

身為神之住所，哈爾曼迪爾·薩希卜的興建理念並不是只限錫克教徒供奉，它其實象徵著對於宗教多元性的開放態度與平等對待<ref name=eos/><ref name="sikhs.org">{{cite web|url=http://www.sikhs.org/granth.htm|title=Sikhism Religion of the Sikh People|work=sikhs.org|accessdate=2016-08-01|archive-date=2017-08-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170804172143/http://www.sikhs.org/granth.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>，為了表示誠意，第五世古魯阿爾瓊在興建此廟之時特別邀請[[伊斯蘭教|伊斯蘭教]][[蘇非主義|蘇非派]]聖者{{Link-en|米安·米爾|Mian Mir}}來奠定廟宇的基石<ref name="Bhatti2013_b">{{cite book|author=S. S. Bhatti|title=Golden Temple: Marvel of Sikh Architecture|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=PJZWQQUyr1EC&pg=PR12|year=2013|publisher=Dorrance Publishing|isbn=978-1-4349-8964-2|pages=12–}}</ref>。哈爾曼迪爾·薩希卜的四個入口也是象徵著歡迎四面八方所來的各教信徒<ref name=Fahlbusch>{{cite book|last=Fahlbusch|first=Erwin|author2=Geoffrey William Bromiley|title=The encyclopedia of Christianity|year=1999|publisher=Brill|location=Leiden|isbn=978-90-04-14596-2|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=lZUBZlth2qgC&pg=PA10&lpg=PA10&dq=harmandir+sahib&source=bl&ots=RdAjNWYmKJ&sig=FEqZjqZHo13SSN3Yrzr9TDNfqG8&hl=en&sa=X&ei=pbxsUJm2FMjWigL48YGYBg&ved=0CD4Q6AEwBDgU#v=onepage&q=harmandir%20sahib&f=false|edition=Reprint|access-date=2016-08-01|archive-date=2014-05-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140507080515/http://books.google.com/books?id=lZUBZlth2qgC&pg=PA10&lpg=PA10&dq=harmandir+sahib&source=bl&ots=RdAjNWYmKJ&sig=FEqZjqZHo13SSN3Yrzr9TDNfqG8&hl=en&sa=X&ei=pbxsUJm2FMjWigL48YGYBg&ved=0CD4Q6AEwBDgU#v=onepage&q=harmandir%20sahib&f=false|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

哈爾曼迪爾·薩希卜每日約有十萬人參訪朝拜，廟內共分12個區域，除聖殿外，還有香客休息室、誦經堂、法師起居室、修道殿、膳廳、儲藏和陳列室等。其中廟内也設有世界最大的免費食堂稱為“{{Link-en|瑯加|Langar (Sikhism)}}”，這個概念由錫克教創始聖人[[古魯那納克|古魯那納克]]提出，同樣為倡導“眾生平等”，不論種族地位、宗教信仰，都能平等地坐在食堂上獲得一頓飯菜的理念。<ref>{{cite news | url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-07-19/india/32745911_1_phone-jammers-mobile-phones-cell-phones | title=Soon, Golden Temple to use phone jammers. Over Two lakh people visit the holy shrine per day for worship. In festivals over six lakh to eight lakh visit the holy shrine. | date=19 July 2012 | work=The Times Of India | accessdate=2016-08-01 | archive-date=2013-01-26 | archive-url=https://archive.today/20130126201851/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-07-19/india/32745911_1_phone-jammers-mobile-phones-cell-phones | dead-url=yes }}</ref>

現今在哈爾曼迪爾‧薩希卜的谒师所為1764年由錫克教領導人{{Link-en|雅薩·辛格·阿魯瓦利亞|Jassa Singh Ahluwalia}}帶領教徒重建的。在19世紀初，[[錫克帝國|錫克帝國]]君主[[兰季德·辛格|兰季德·辛格]]派人將其表面鋪上一層金箔，據說金色的廟頂共用去了750公斤的黃金，故得其別名“金廟”。<ref name="MLH">{{cite book|last=Hew McLeod|first=|title=Sikhism|url=https://archive.org/details/sikhism00mcle|year=1997|publisher=Penguin Books|location=New York|isbn=0-14-025260-6|pages=[https://archive.org/details/sikhism00mcle/page/154 154]–161}}</ref>
